title: SpaceX crew to return to Earth after six-month ISS Stay
summary: After more than six months in space, four people are set to splashdown in the waters near Florida. The SpaceX Crew-6 mission, which launched on March 2 and docked with the International Space Station (ISS) the following day, will undock on Sept. 3 at 7:05 EDT (11:05 UTC). Recovery vessels are ready to retrieve the crew and their capsule, Crew Dragon Endeavour (C206), from either the Gulf of Mexico or the Atlantic Ocean with the help of support vessel Shannon or Megan in the early morning hours of Sept. 4.

title: Lockheed Martin, NASA lining up next Orion spacecraft for Artemis III and IV
summary: Orion prime contractor Lockheed Martin has the spacecraft for NASA’s Artemis III and IV lunar landing missions in production alongside the Artemis II vehicle that is going into final assembly at the Kennedy Space Center (KSC) in Florida. Simultaneous assembly and test of three Orions is becoming the norm, as the Orion program works towards its goal of delivering one spacecraft every year for eventual, annual Artemis missions.

title: Coverage Set as NASA’s SpaceX Crew-6 Prepares for Splashdown
summary: NASA will provide coverage of the agency’s SpaceX Crew-6 mission return to Earth from the International Space Station, beginning with hatch closure coverage live at 5 a.m. EDT on Sunday, Sept. 3.

title: SpaceX launches 13 satellites for U.S. Space Development Agency
summary: A SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket lifted off Sept. 2 at 7:25 a.m. Pacific from Launch Complex 4 East at Vandenberg Space Force Base, California, carrying 13 U.S. military satellites.

title: Microsoft Partners With Synthetaic On AI And Data Analysis
summary: Microsoft Corporation has announced a five-year partnership with Synthetaic, a Wisconsin-based startup specializing in utilizing artificial intelligence (AI) to analyze data from space and air sensors.

title: NASA Prepares For OSIRIS-REx Asteroid Sample ReEntry & Landing
summary: A team led by NASA in Utah’s West Desert are in the final stages of preparing for the arrival of the first US asteroid sample which will return to Earth this September.

title: NASA Confirms New Frontiers Program Delay
summary: NASA's Science Mission Directorate (SMD) has confirmed that the call for proposals for the next New Frontiers planetary science mission will be delayed until no earlier than 2026.

title: India launches first solar research mission, Aditya-L1, aboard PSLV
summary: India’s space program continued its busy 2023 with the launch of its first solar research mission, Aditya-L1, on Saturday. Liftoff, aboard the country’s Polar Satellite Launch Vehicle (PSLV) XL rocket, occurred at 11:50 Indian Standard Time (06:20 UTC) from the Satish Dhawan Space Centre.

title: NASA’s LRO Spots Likely Luna-25 Crash Site
